==Events== *[[AD 999|999]] &ndash; [[Battle of Glenmama]]: The combined forces of [[Munster]] and [[Kingdom of Meath|Meath]] under king [[Brian Boru]] inflict a crushing defeat on the allied armies of [[Leinster]] and [[Kingdom of Dublin|Dublin]] near [[Lyons Hill]] in [[Ireland]]. *[[1066]] &ndash; [[1066 Granada massacre|Granada massacre]]: A [[Islam|Muslim]] mob storms the royal palace in [[Granada]], crucifies [[Jews|Jewish]] [[vizier]] Joseph ibn Naghrela and massacres most of the Jewish population of the city. *[[1419]] &ndash; [[Hundred Years' War (1415–53)|Hundred Years' War]]: [[Battle of La Rochelle (1419)|Battle of La Rochelle]]. *[[1460]] &ndash; [[Wars of the Roses]]: Lancastrians kill the [[Richard of York, 3rd Duke of York|3rd Duke of York]] and win the [[Battle of Wakefield]]. *[[1702]] &ndash; [[Queen Anne's War]]: [[James Moore (South Carolina politician)|James Moore]], Governor of the [[Province of Carolina]], abandons the [[Siege of St. Augustine (1702)|Siege of St. Augustine]]. *[[1813]] &ndash; [[War of 1812]]: British soldiers [[Battle of Buffalo|burn Buffalo]], New York. *[[1816]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of St. Louis (1816)|Treaty of St. Louis]] between the United States and the united [[Odawa|Ottawa]], [[Ojibwe|Ojibwa]], and [[Potawatomi]] Indian tribes is proclaimed. *[[1825]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of St. Louis (1825)|Treaty of St. Louis]] between the United States and the [[Shawnee]] Nation is proclaimed. *[[1853]] &ndash; [[Gadsden Purchase]]: The United States buys land from Mexico to facilitate [[Rail transport|railroad]] building in the [[Southwestern United States|Southwest]]. *[[1890]] &ndash; Following the [[Wounded Knee Massacre]], the [[United States Army]] and [[Lakota people|Lakota]] warriors face off in the [[Drexel Mission Fight]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.buffalosoldiers-washington.com/MajorHenrySep24.html|title=Major Guy V. Henry and the 9th Cavalry's Great Cavalry Ride|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> *[[1896]] &ndash; Filipino patriot and reform advocate [[José Rizal]] is executed by a Spanish [[Execution by firing squad|firing squad]] in [[Manila]]. *1896 &ndash; Canadian [[ice hockey]] player [[Ernie McLea]] scores the first [[hat-trick]] in [[Stanley Cup]] play, and the Cup-winning goal as the [[Montreal Victorias]] defeat the [[Winnipeg Victorias]] 6–5. *[[1897]] &ndash; The British [[Colony of Natal]] annexes [[Zulu Kingdom|Zululand]]. *[[1903]] &ndash; [[Iroquois Theatre fire|A fire at the Iroquois Theater]] in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]] kills at least 605. *[[1905]] &ndash; Former [[Idaho]] Governor [[Frank Steunenberg]] is assassinated at the front gate of his home in [[Caldwell, Idaho|Caldwell]]. *[[1906]] &ndash; The [[All-India Muslim League]] is founded in [[Dhaka|Dacca]], [[East Bengal]], British India (later [[Dhaka, Bangladesh]]). *[[1916]] &ndash; Russian mystic and advisor to the Tsar [[Grigori Yefimovich Rasputin]] was murdered by a loyalist group led by Prince [[Felix Yusupov]]. His frozen, partially-trussed body was discovered in a Moscow river three days later. * 1916 &ndash; The last [[coronation of the Hungarian monarch|coronation in Hungary]] is performed for King [[Charles I of Austria|Charles IV]] and Queen [[Zita of Bourbon-Parma|Zita]]. *[[1922]] &ndash; The [[Soviet Union|Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]] [[Treaty on the Creation of the USSR|is formed]]. *[[1927]] &ndash; The [[Tokyo Metro Ginza Line|Ginza Line]], the first [[rapid transit|subway line]] in Asia, opens in Tokyo, Japan. *[[1935]] &ndash; The Italian Air Force [[Dolo hospital airstrike|bombs a Swedish Red Cross hospital]] during the [[Second Italo-Abyssinian War]]. *[[1936]] &ndash; The [[United Auto Workers]] [[trade union|union]] stages its first [[sitdown strike]]. *[[1943]] &ndash; [[Subhas Chandra Bose]] raises the flag of Indian independence at [[Port Blair]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; King [[George II of Greece]] declares a regency, leaving the throne vacant. *[[1947]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: King [[Michael I of Romania]] is forced to abdicate by the Soviet Union-backed Communist government of [[Romania]]. *[[1952]] &ndash; An RAF [[Avro Lancaster]] bomber [[1952 Luqa Avro Lancaster crash|crashed]] in [[Luqa]], Malta after an engine failure, killing three crew members and a civilian on the ground.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Caruana |first1=Richard |title=60 years ago: Lancaster crashes into Luqa village |url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/60-years-ago-lancaster-crashes-into-luqa-village.451515 |work=[[Times of Malta]] |date=30 December 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215180324/https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/60-years-ago-lancaster-crashes-into-luqa-village.451515 |archivedate=15 February 2020}}</ref> *[[1958]] &ndash; The [[Guatemalan Air Force]] sinks several Mexican fishing boats alleged to have breached maritime borders, killing three and sparking [[Mexico-Guatemala conflict|international tension]]. *[[1965]] &ndash; [[Ferdinand Marcos]] becomes [[President of the Philippines]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The United States halts heavy bombing of [[North Vietnam]]. *[[1993]] &ndash; [[Israel]] establishes [[diplomatic recognition|diplomatic relations]] with [[Holy See|Vatican City]] and also upgrades to full diplomatic relations with [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. *[[1996]] &ndash; Proposed budget cuts by [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] spark protests from 250,000 workers who shut down services across [[Israel]]. *[[1997]] &ndash; In the worst incident in [[Algeria]]'s insurgency, the [[Wilaya of Relizane massacres of 30 December 1997|Wilaya of Relizane massacres]], 400 people from four villages are killed. *[[2000]] &ndash; [[Rizal Day bombings]]: A series of bombs explode in various places in [[Metro Manila]], Philippines within a period of a few hours, killing 22 and injuring about a hundred. *[[2004]] &ndash; A fire in the [[República Cromañón nightclub fire|República Cromagnon nightclub]] in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] kills 194. *[[2005]] &ndash; [[Tropical Storm Zeta]] forms in the open Atlantic Ocean, tying the record for the latest [[tropical cyclone]] ever to form in the North Atlantic basin. *[[2006]] &ndash; [[Madrid–Barajas Airport]] is [[2006 Madrid-Barajas Airport bombing|bombed]]. *2006 &ndash; The Indonesian passenger ferry {{MV|Senopati Nusantara}} sinks in a storm, resulting in at least 400 deaths. *2006 &ndash; Former [[President of Iraq]] [[Saddam Hussein]] [[Execution of Saddam Hussein|is executed]]. *[[2009]] &ndash; A segment of the [[Lanzhou–Zhengzhou–Changsha pipeline]] ruptures in [[Shaanxi]], China, and approximately {{convert|150000|l|usgal|abbr=on}} of [[Diesel fuel|diesel oil]] [[Yellow River oil spill|flows down]] the [[Wei River]] before finally reaching the [[Yellow River]]. *2009 &ndash; A suicide bomber [[Camp Chapman attack|kills]] nine people at [[Forward Operating Base Chapman]], a key facility of the [[Central Intelligence Agency]] in [[Afghanistan]]. *[[2013]] &ndash; More than 100 people are killed when anti-government forces [[December 2013 Kinshasa attacks|attack]] key buildings in [[Kinshasa]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
